The White House has announced Hedieh "Roshan" Ghaffarian as the new White House Chief Floral Designer. First Lady Michelle Obama expressed excitement about Ghaffarian's appointment, highlighting her diverse portfolio and the opportunity for her creativity to flourish. White House Social Secretary Deesha Dyer also praised Ghaffarian's entrepreneurial spirit and artistry. Ghaffarian, who was born in Tehran, Iran, and raised in California, started her own business called Flower Affairs in her early twenties. She has over 25 years of experience and has completed over 1,000 events. Ghaffarian has trained with renowned floral designers from the UK and her work has been featured in various publications. She will begin her full-time role on October 18, starting with the China State Dinner.